Normally Vue-router can successfuly pass data with name params combination

```javascript
let object = {data: 'someData'}

this.$router.push({
   name:'PageName',
   params: {object}
})
```

But when I use path, params is truncated. Is there a way that Vue-router can pass objects safely?

```javascript
let object = {data: 'someData'}

this.$router.push({
   path: 'page/name',
   params: {object}
})
```

### Version
3.0.1

### Reproduction link
[https://codepen.io/anon/pen/gKNYwO?editors=1010](https://codepen.io/anon/pen/gKNYwO?editors=1010)

### Steps to reproduce
import AnyComponent from './Somewhere';

const router = new VueRouter({ 
  routes: [], 
  mode: 'history'
});

new Vue({ router });

router.addRoutes([{ path:'/example', name: 'example', component: AnyComponent }]);

### What is expected?
console.log(router.options.routes); // [{ path:'/example', name: 'example', component: AnyComponent }]

### What is actually happening?
console.log(router.options.routes); // []

---
Shouldn't update router.options.routes when using router.addRoutes?

